# Edge Platform Context

## Tech Stack
- **Frontend**: React 18 + TypeScript, Vite, Tailwind CSS, Playwright E2E tests
- **Backend**: FastAPI (Python 3.11), SQLAlchemy async models, Pydantic v2
- **Deployment**: Railway (Dockerfile builder), GitHub repo `iambrands/edgedemo-ai`
- **Production URL**: `https://edgedemo-ai-production.up.railway.app`

## Architecture
- No production database yet — all DB-dependent routers use **mock data fallbacks**
- `backend/app.py` checks `_db_available` at startup; if false, skips real routers and mounts mock versions from `backend/api/mock_endpoints.py`
- Mock portal API at `backend/api/mock_portal.py` serves client portal data
- Frontend SPA served by FastAPI's `StaticFiles` mount from `frontend/dist/`

## Auth
- **RIA Login**: `backend/api/auth.py` — standalone JWT (bcrypt + python-jose), no DB needed
- **Client Portal**: `backend/services/portal_auth_service.py` — separate JWT for portal users
- **Demo credential**: `leslie@iabadvisors.com` / `CreateWealth2026$`

## Branding
- Product name is **Edge** (not "EdgeAI")
- Colors: blue (`#2563EB`), white, green (`#10B981`)
- Left sidebar nav has blue background with collapsible menu groups
- AI chat widget floats bottom-right on every dashboard page

## Key Directories
- `frontend/src/pages/dashboard/` — RIA advisor pages
- `frontend/src/pages/portal/` — Client portal pages
- `frontend/src/components/ui/` — Shared UI primitives (Card, Button, Badge, etc.)
- `backend/api/` — FastAPI routers
- `backend/api/mock_endpoints.py` — Mock data for all DB-dependent features
- `frontend/e2e/` — Playwright E2E tests
